\i Notes on the "fully Authored" DVD assets:\i0\par
\par
\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\cf1\b\f1\fs28 1) the Original 7-minute pre-rendered intro\cf0\b0\f0\fs20\par
\pard\par
This was shown at the 2000 Computer Game Developer's Conference (along with\par
in-game footage, some of which ended up in the 2001 E3 trailer) to rapturous\par
applause.  The importance of the Nomads that is inferred from their role in this intro\par
caused concern for us, as it warrants an early introduction to Nomads in the\par
story.  The intro movie was completely rendered before the rest of Freelancer's\par
story had been put together.  Over time, we decided that introducing the Nomads later\par
in the game was a better idea, and so we "removed" them from the intro - which is why\par
we have an "Original" intro and a "Release" intro.\par
\tab Note - you can use the "audio" button on your DVD remote to change\par
soundtracks - We've separated out the music, sound-effects and dialogue for those\par
who want to hear them separately.  Assignments are as follows:\par
\tab\tab Audio Soundtrack 1 (default) = mix\par
\tab\tab Audio Soundtrack 2 = fx\par
\tab\tab Audio Soundtrack 3 = music\par
\tab\tab Audio Soundtrack 4 = dialogue\par
\par
\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\cf1\b\f1\fs28 2) the Release version of the pre-rendered intro\cf0\b0\f0\fs20\par
\pard\par
This is the version that ships with the game - but it has the 5.1 soundmix applied,\par
and of course the picture is "DVD quality." (The Release version on the game CD\par
had a 2.0-channel sound mix and used the Windows Media 7 codec.)\par
\par
\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\cf1\b\f1\fs28 3) the "restored RTC intro"\cf0\b0\f0\fs20\par
\pard\par
In early versions of the game, the intro sequences continued for a total of 11 minutes,\par
which we deemed too long to get players into the action; therefore we removed\par
this section from the game.  It was to have played in between the pre-rendered intro\par
and the Freeport Seven Disaster sequence.  Here it is, restored for your viewing\par
pleasure, now pre-rendered at NTSC resolution with 16x anti-aliasing.  Note - the\par
soundtrack is a temp track specially-created for this DVD - the sequence was cut from\par
the game before any final music and sound-effects were done.  This intro is of\par
particular interest to anyone wondering where that egg-shaped "artifact" came from.\par
\par
\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\cf1\b\f1\fs28 4) trailers\cf0\b0\f0\fs20\par
\pard\par
These are the only trailers we produced for the game.  The 2001 trailer was created by\par
Digital Anvil's video editor Curtis Neal and Project Lead Phil Wattenbarger, and\par
features music by James Hannigan.  The 2002 trailer started life as an "unofficial,\par
underground trailer" by RTC editor Ray Barerra.  Phil Wattenbarger liked it so much\par
that it became the official trailer for E3 that year - after getting music from James\par
Hannigan and Mat Mitchell.  The "web trailer" was put together around the time of the\par
release of the game, by Curtis Neal.\par
\par
\par
\pard{\pntext\f3\'B7\tab}{\*\pn\pnlvlblt\pnf3\pnindent0{\pntxtb\'B7}}\fi-720\li720\cf1\b\f1\fs28 5) Concept Art\cf0\b0\f0\fs20\par
\pard\par
We included many sketches from 1997/1998/1999 and you can see that we had many ideas on\par
how and where to take the characters in the game.  Adam Medhurst was Freelancer's Art\par
Director back then.  The Nomads underwent the largest changes of all from concept to\par
release; they are not portrayed "walking around" in the released game, though we\par
considered the concept.\par
\par
